  </div>

  <!-- USAGE GUIDE -->

  <div class="guide-card">
    <h3>How to Use This in Google Forms</h3>
    <p>Copy each question above directly into a new Google Form. Set your form theme to match (dark green header if available, or leave default — the content does the work). Make sure you:</p>
    <p><strong>1. Set the form to "collect email addresses"</strong> automatically via Google Forms settings — this captures emails even if someone doesn't fill in Q2, and gives you a clean export.</p>
    <p><strong>2. Send privately, not publicly.</strong> Share the link only via direct DM or personal message — never post it publicly. The exclusivity framing in the header only works if it genuinely is private. Say something like: <em>"Sharing this with a small group before we go public — thought of you specifically."</em></p>
    <p><strong>3. Watch Q7 (intent) closely.</strong> Count "Definitely" + "Very Likely" responses in real time. Once you hit 25+ strong responses from your private list, you have strong evidence the event will sell. That's when you open early bird.</p>
    <p><strong>4. Use Q11 answers as content.</strong> Export the open text responses — they are your copywriting brief. The exact phrases people use to describe their pain are the phrases you should use in your promotional posts.</p>
    <p><strong>5. Follow up personally within 48 hours.</strong> Anyone who answers "Definitely" gets a personal DM or message from you — before any ticket link exists. That personal contact is what converts interest into a sale.</p>
  </div>

</div>

<script>
  // Make options feel interactive
  document.querySelectorAll('.option').forEach(option => {
    option.addEventListener('click', function() {
      const input = this.querySelector('input');
      if (input.type === 'radio') {
        const name = input.name;
        document.querySelectorAll(`input[name="${name}"]`).forEach(r => {
          r.closest('.option').classList.remove('selected');
        });
        this.classList.add('selected');
      } else {
        this.classList.toggle('selected');
      }
    });
  });

  // Scale buttons
  document.querySelectorAll('.scale-option').forEach(btn => {
    btn.addEventListener('click', function() {
      this.classList.toggle('active');
    });
  });
</script>

